OL,3,CHorse expert jailed for life for
OL,4,Ckilling husband at home
OL,6,FShe pleaded not guilty to a charge of
OL,7,Fmurder, claiming she was acting in
OL,8,Fself-defence following years of abuse
OL,9,Fat the hands of her husband, but was
OL,10,Fconvicted of the charge by a unanimous
OL,11,Fjury on Friday 22 March.
OL,13,FJudge James Adkin told Rawle she
OL,14,F"violently thrust" a knife with a 12.5-
OL,15,Finch blade into her husband's back,
OL,16,Fintending to kill him, during a heated
OL,17,Fargument about the sale of land on
OL,18,Ftheir #800,000 home.
