OL,6,FDuring the trial, Rawle claimed she
OL,7,Fhad been the victim of coercive and
OL,8,Fcontrolling behaviour ` suffering
OL,9,Fyears of physical and psychological
OL,10,Fabuse from her husband.
OL,12,FThe judge said: "Ian was not perfect.
OL,13,FThe evidence showed that he was
OL,14,Fobstinate, sometimes grumpy, he could
OL,15,Fshout, he was stuck in his ways and he
OL,16,Fwas old-fashioned in terms of how he
OL,17,Fwanted a relationship with his wife.
OL,19,F"But he was in no way the serial
OL,20,Fdomestic abuser you sought to portray
OL,21,Fhim as."
